news.title: Nashik civic body rakes in 50% of total property tax via online mode
news.para: Before the Covid-19 pandemic, NMC's online property tax payment was only 7%. This shift towards digital payments indicated a growing trend towards online convenience.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body's revenue committee  approves property tax incentive rebate scheme
news.para: The AMC announces the scheme annually on March 1. It is estimated that the scheme will generate over Rs 250 crore in revenue.

news.title: TCS to acquire Darshita Southern India Happy Homes for Rs 2,250 crore
news.para: This acquisition involves the purchase of 100% equity shares, giving the acquiring firm complete ownership of the entity.

news.title: Maharashtra deputy CM announces panel on Gunthewari Act issues in Nagpur
news.para: Raising the issue in the assembly, BJP MLA Pravin Datke highlighted that approximately 1.5 lakh plot holders in Nagpur had applied for regularisation under the Gunthewari Act, but even after two years, they have not received release letters.

news.title: Aditya Birla Cap infuses Rs 300 crore in housing finance arm via rights issue
news.para: "Aditya Birla Capital has made an investment of ₹300 crore on a rights basis in the equity shares of Aditya Birla Housing Finance," according to a stock exchange filing.

news.title: Lucknow development body files claims against Ansals, puts maps on hold
news.para: This decision will remain in effect until the department completes its scrutiny of land records and related documents or until the case is finalised and a decision is taken by the govt.

news.title: Karnataka REAT orders promoter to pay interest on refund
news.para: Though they were refunded Rs 51.4 lakh advance they had paid, they were denied interest. The Karnataka Real Estate Appellate Tribunal (KREAT) recently ordered the project promoter to pay interest on their refunded amount.

news.title: Home buyers want Karnataka RERA to implement project closure policy
news.para: They complain that many builders have failed to complete housing projects on time, and RERA Karnataka has not taken any steps to ensure that builders submit reports on project completion.

news.title: Cops not implementing Haryana RERA orders: Adjudicating officer
news.para: He said while the ombudsman's inefficiency has repeatedly come under Supreme Court's scrutiny, Rera will be a "paper tiger" if this is how the system behaves, seeking govt's intervention to change things.

news.title: Kalyan tehsildar directs police to register FIR on builder over forged land records
news.para: Shiv Sena (UBT) district president Dipesh Mhatre, who has been following up on the revenue department's action in the case, obtained land records of some of the errant builders and found that one of them had prepared the forged documents.

news.title: Court stays trial proceedings against M3M Realty's MD in Ireo group case
news.para: The court, presided over by Rajeev Goyal, issued the stay following an application filed by Bansal last year. Bansal, who was arrested by the ED in 2022, had been facing trial in the case.

news.title: Allahabad HC cautions Uttar Pradesh govt over use of private land sans due legal process
news.para: Allowing the plea of one Kanyawati from Bareilly district, the court said, "The state authorities are required to be cautious that they should not utilise the land of the citizens without due authority of law or without following the proper procedure of acquisition."

news.title: Adani Group wins Rs 36,000 crore Motital Nagar redevelopment project in Mumbai
news.para: Adani Properties Pvt Ltd (APPL) emerged as the highest bidder, offering more built-up area than its nearest rival, L&T, sources aware of the matter said.

news.title: Tayal Corp : Trendsetters in Pune’s real estate
news.para: Led by Ar. Sumit Tayal, Tayal Corp. is not just another real estate developer; it is a collective of thinkers, visionaries, and problem-solvers who operate with an intrinsic understanding of form, function, and integrity.

news.title: ETRECA 2025: Shaping the future of Indian real estate
news.para: ETRECA 2025 opened with keynote addresses from Anand Kumar, chairman, Delhi RERA, and Sanjay R. Bhoosreddy, chairman, Uttar Pradesh RERA.

news.title: SIPCOT industrial park will be set up on 800 acres land in Cheyyur: Tamil Nadu CM
news.para: He laid foundation stones for five new projects valued at Rs 497.6 crore and provided government welfare assistance worth Rs 508.3 crore to 50,606 beneficiaries on the occasion.

news.title: Omaxe to invest Rs 600 crore in Faridabad’s retail project
news.para: The development is part of Omaxe World Street, 27 acre of which is already operational and has over 250 brands.

news.title: Jharkhand government plans for tax on lands being used for commercial purposes: Minister
news.para: He emphasised that the government's initiative aims to enhance transparency in land-related matters, which have a significant impact on the state's law and order situation.

news.title: UK's Persimmon to build more homes after 2024 profit beats estimates
news.para: The forecast comes as affordability remains a concern in Britain's housing sector. Interest rate cuts by the Bank of England are expected to provide some support, but there is uncertainty over the pace of further monetary easing and domestic growth.

news.title: Panaji smart city completes 42 projects
news.para: Minister of state in the ministry of housing and urban affairs, Tokhan Sahu, released the information in the Rajya Sabha.
